com.viaoa.hub
Interface HubListener<T>

All Superinterfaces:
java.util.EventListener
All Known Implementing Classes:
ButtonController, ComboBoxController, CustomComboBoxController, DateChooserController, FormattedTextFieldController, HTMLTextPaneController, Hub2TextFieldLookup, Hub2TreeNode, HubAutoMatch, HubAutoSequence, HubCacheAdder, HubCopy, HubFilter, HubListenerAdapter, HubShareAO, HubSortListener, JFCController, LabelController, ListController, TextAreaController, TextFieldController, ToggleButtonController
public interface HubListener<T>
extends java.util.EventListener

The only event listener definition for receiving events from OAObject, Hub, and OAObjectCacheController.

Both Hub and OAObjectCacheController allow for HubListeners to be registered.
OAObject sends events through the Hubs that it is a member of, and through the OAObjectCacheController.

See Also:
HubEvent, Hub.addListener, OAObjectCacheController#addListener

Method Detail

beforePropertyChange

void beforePropertyChange(HubEvent<T> e)
Event sent whenever a property is changed. This includes OAObject or Hub properties.
OAObject: any object property, changed, editable, new
Hub: allowDelete, allowNew, allowEdit, eof, bof

Note: propertyChanges are sent for any changed object, not just the ActiveObject

See Also:
OAObject.fireBeforePropertyChange, Hub.firePropertyChange
